    "body": "`window.setAlwaysOnTop(true, \"screen-saver\")` sets the window level to `NSScreenSaverWindowLevel`, and it does that, so this is not a bug and I'm closing this issue.\n\nFor allowing the window to be placed above the menu bar, you have to find the solution yourself, and we will be very happy to add a new API or option for it.\n"
